Czech Republic to Cut Spending by $1.7 Billion, Hospodarske Says

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-07-13T05:46:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/czech-republic-to-cut-spending-by-1-7-billion-hospodarske-says.html
The  Czech Republic  needs to cut
spending by 30 billion koruna ($1.7 billion) to keep the 2012
budget deficit at 105 billion koruna,  Hospodarske Noviny 
reported, citing Finance Minister Miroslav Kalousek.  The government plans to further reduce the budgets of
individual ministries and cut scheduled spending on highways by
14 billion koruna, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story: Lenka Ponikelska in
Prague   lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  